    <title>CrowdStrike has a new guidance hub for dealing with the Windows outage</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="Vector illustration of the Crowdstrike logo." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ngl-jPiaFJ7S5R_pfsbMWE5N0Pg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73473133/STK275_CROWDSTRIKE_CVIRGINIA_A.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Image: The Verge&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="GW9J05"&gt;CrowdStrike has published a new “&lt;a href="https://www.crowdstrike.com/falcon-content-update-remediation-and-guidance-hub/"&gt;Remediation and Guidance Hub&lt;/a&gt;” that collects details related to its faulty update that &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/20/24202527/crowdstrike-microsoft-windows-bsod-outage"&gt;crashed 8.5 million Windows computers&lt;/a&gt; across the globe on Friday. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="4Psb8J"&gt;The page includes technical information on what caused the outage, what systems are affected, and &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/19/24202255/the-crowdstrike-ceos-latest-apology"&gt;CEO George Kurtz’s statement&lt;/a&gt;. It contains links to Bitlocker key recovery processes and to various third-party vendor pages about dealing with the outage, as well. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="c-float-left c-float-hang"&gt;&lt;aside id="2a1qr2"&gt;&lt;div data-anthem-component="readmore" data-anthem-component-data='{"stories":[{"title":"Microsoft releases recovery tool to help repair Windows machines hit by CrowdStrike issue","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/21/24202883/microsoft-recovery-tool-windows-crowdstrike-issue-it-admins"},{"title":"CrowdStrike’s faulty update crashed 8.5 million Windows devices, says Microsoft","url":"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/20/24202527/crowdstrike-microsoft-windows-bsod-outage"}]}'&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/aside&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p id="N5v5wp"&gt;The page points to a knowledge base article (which only logged-in customers can access) for using a bootable USB key. Microsoft &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/21/24202883/microsoft-recovery-tool-windows-crowdstrike-issue-it-admins"&gt;released such a tool yesterday&lt;/a&gt; that automatically deletes the problematic channel file that caused machines to blue screen.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="kPsUEh"&gt;CrowdStrike also &lt;a href="https://www.crowdstrike.com/blog/likely-ecrime-actor-capitalizing-on-falcon-sensor-issues/"&gt;published a blog yesterday...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;
    &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/21/24202923/crowdstrike-remediation-guidance-hub-windows-bsods-outage-malware"&gt;Continue reading&amp;hellip;&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/p&gt;

</content>
